T1  - On the Number and Size of Nations*
PY  - 1997
Y1  - 1997/11/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355300555411
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 112
IS  - 4
SP  - 1027
EP  - 1056
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper studies the equilibrium determination of the number of countries in different political regimes, and in different economic environments, with more or less economic integration. We focus on the trade-off between the benefits of large jurisdictions and the costs of heterogeneity of large and diverse populations. Our model implies that (i) democratization leads to secessions; (ii) in equilibrium one generally observes an inefficiently large number of countries; (iii) the equilibrium number of countries is increasing in the amount of economic integration.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355300555411
ER  - 



